      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BYE BYE TAIPAN (1) well back settling but did wind up strongly to finish 5th and beaten only 1.5 lengths (20.15) at this track. Form here at the trip sound including four wins. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Better than the latest effort and deserves another chance. OUTBACK GOLD (2) wasn't far away at the finish when 5th and beaten only 5 lengths (20.35) at this track. Form here at the trip sound including eight wins. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Worth another chance. MRS. ESHAY (7) has missed the frame at her last two but did run well three back when third (20.21) in a P5 at this track. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. GOLD TIP (3) with some luck can improve on an unplaced run last time here.",
